cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with emulating shared memory in distributed systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for shared memory emulation.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses erasure coding methods.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with distributed systems and their control.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with message-passing architectures.
